text: Ixora mooreensis is a species of flowering plant in the family Rubiaceae. It is endemic to Moorea in French Polynesia, hence its name. ==Sources== * Florence, J. 1998. Ixora moorensis. 2006 IUCN Red List of Threatened Species.
